Class GenomicDNASequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.iastate.cs228.hw1.Sequence

  • public class GenomicDNASequence
extends DNASequence
    This class extends the class DNASequence. The class GenomicDNASequence has a constructor and a method, but has no additional field. A genomic DNA sequence often codes a gene with separate protein-coding parts called exons, with parts between/before/after them called introns / intergenic regions.
    Author:
    Ram Luitel
